items.definition: The difference in the CO2 fugacity (effective partial pressure allowing for non-ideal gas) between air in equilibrium with seawater and the atmosphere

prefLabel._value: Fugacity anomaly (water - air) of carbon dioxide in the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of the specified pigment determined by HPLC assay of a sample collected by dissolution in acteone of the residue collected by GF/F filtration of a known volume of any water body. The quoted value either results from a single determination or the average of replicate determinations

prefLabel._value: Concentration of echinenone per unit mass of the water body

items.definition: The relative representation of flora and fauna in a particular sample or region.
The identification of the biotic elements to the relevant scientific classification group (taxa), e.g. genus or species.
Light extinction coefficient (490nm wavelength) in the water body by radiometer and computation from variation of light intensity with depth.

prefLabel._value: Light extinction coefficient (490nm wavelength) in the water body

items.definition: The force per unit area exerted by the overlying sea water, sea ice, air and any other medium that may be present on a sensor located in the water column.

prefLabel._value: Pressure (measured variable) in the water body exerted by overlying sea water and any medium above it

items.definition: The force per unit area exerted by the overlying sea water on a sensor located in the water column. Excludes the pressure due to sea ice, air and any other medium that may be present.

prefLabel._value: Pressure (measured variable) in the water body exerted by overlying sea water only
Dry weight biomass per unit volume of the water body
Wet weight biomass per unit volume of the water body
Downwelling vector irradiance as photons (PAR wavelengths) in the atmosphere
